"{\"uid\": \"mercurynews.com-2024-07-27-summer-olympics-katie-ledecky-wins-first-heat-to-compete-for-first-gold-medal-saturday-afternoon\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Today's e-Edition  Get Morning Report and other email newsletters    Get Morning Report and other email newsletters  Today's e-Edition  Trending:  Ariarne Titmus knocked off Katie Ledecky again at the Olympics, winning the 400-meter freestyle Saturday in one of the most highly anticipated races of the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 315, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 147, \"end\": 161, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ariarne Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ariarne_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 174, \"end\": 187, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus, the Australian star known as \\\"The Terminator,\\\" handed the Stanford grad a second straight defeat in an event the American won at Rio de Janeiro in 2016.\", \"from\": 317, \"to\": 477, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 317, \"end\": 323, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 329, \"end\": 344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian_Star\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Australian star\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian_Star\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Australian_Star\"}, {\"begin\": 383, \"end\": 391, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1939028373032165e-25, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}, {\"begin\": 438, \"end\": 446, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9760899087697784, \"rank\": 0.018359605802327785, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 454, \"end\": 468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.990868702708121e-21, \"text\": \"Rio de Janeiro\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rio_de_Janeiro\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With her fingernails painted Aussie yellow, Titmus led from start to finish.\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 555, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 523, \"end\": 529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She faced her stiffest challenge from Canadian phenom Summer McIntosh but won comfortably in 3 minutes, 57.49 seconds.\", \"from\": 556, \"to\": 674, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 602, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"score\": 0.999999902955101, \"rank\": 9.704508037193928e-08, \"text\": \"Canadian\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Canadians\"}, {\"begin\": 610, \"end\": 625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Summer McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Summer_McIntosh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McIntosh claimed the silver in 3:58.37.\", \"from\": 676, \"to\": 715, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1714341707497228e-13, \"text\": \"McIntosh\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McIntosh_Laboratory\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky never threatened in the race and got the bronze in 4:00.86.\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 783, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I just did not have it on the last 200 or 250 that way I wanted to,\\\"Ledecky told reporters in Paris.\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 886, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 885, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.212082646559151e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I felt like my first 150 was pretty good.\", \"from\": 887, \"to\": 929, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I went out with the field and felt like I was within striking distance.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just could not kick in into that next gear that I would have wanted to finish it out.\\\"\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1090, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky entered the Summer Olympics with six gold medals, one shy of tying Jenny Thompson for most ever by a female swimmer and two shy of matching the all-time record for gold medals by a female Olympian.\", \"from\": 1092, \"to\": 1297, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1167, \"end\": 1181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jenny Thompson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jenny_Thompson\"}, {\"begin\": 1288, \"end\": 1296, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999998960929642, \"rank\": 1.0390723834908816e-07, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She's gone back and forth with Titmus over the years.\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1330, \"end\": 1336, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While Ledecky has the Olympic record in the 400-meter freestyle with a 3:56.46, set at the 2016 Games, Titmus took home the gold in Tokyo and currently holds the world record with a 3:55.38.\", \"from\": 1353, \"to\": 1543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1456, \"end\": 1462, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1485, \"end\": 1490, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.416665505438882e-14, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Titmus now has three individual Olympic victories on her growing resume.\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1551, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She swept the 200 and 400 free in Tokyo and is favored to pull off the same double in Paris.\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.416665505438882e-14, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1704, \"end\": 1709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.212082646559151e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ledecky is not done yet.\", \"from\": 1712, \"to\": 1736, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"She skipped a chance to face Titmus again in the 200 free, but the American is favored to take gold in both the 800 and 1,500.\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1766, \"end\": 1772, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Titmus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fred_Titmus\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9760899087697784, \"rank\": 0.018359605802327785, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stanford's Torri Huske and Simone Manuel joined Kate Douglass and Gretchen Walsh to capture a silver medal in the women's 4\\u00d7100 freestyle relay.\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 2009, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1939028373032165e-25, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}, {\"begin\": 1876, \"end\": 1887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Torri Huske\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Torri_Huske\"}, {\"begin\": 1892, \"end\": 1905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Manuel\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Manuel\"}, {\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kate Douglass\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kate_Douglass\"}, {\"begin\": 1931, \"end\": 1945, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gretchen Walsh\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gretchen_Walsh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They could not catch the Australian women, who set an Olympic record with a winning time of 3:28.92.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2110, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2035, \"end\": 2045, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"score\": 0.5602572795611448, \"rank\": 0.7839626559726479, \"text\": \"Australian\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_national_cricket_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Huske also won her heat in the 100-meter butterfly with a 57.72 time to qualify for the semifinals.\", \"from\": 2112, \"to\": 2211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the semifinals, she won her heat with a time of 56:00, earning her a spot in the finals on Sunday.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2314, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jack Alexy, a Cal junior who won NCAA national championships in 2022 and 2023, opened for the men's 4\\u00d7100 relay team that won a gold medal on Saturday.\", \"from\": 2316, \"to\": 2467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2316, \"end\": 2320, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"score\": 0.5613976022485366, \"rank\": 0.7572128509706546, \"text\": \"Jack\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jack_Shephard\"}, {\"begin\": 2330, \"end\": 2333, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.66535662365962e-18, \"text\": \"Cal\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/California_Golden_Bears\"}, {\"begin\": 2349, \"end\": 2353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"score\": 0.9999954841448118, \"rank\": 4.515872201550442e-06, \"text\": \"NCAA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Collegiate_Athletic_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alexy got off to a decent start and was two seconds behind the Chinese team after the first leg, but Chris Guiliano made up ground in the second leg put Team USA ahead.\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2532, \"end\": 2539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9483548174726091, \"rank\": 0.05288844190110809, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2622, \"end\": 2630, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9976628301718733, \"rank\": 0.0023426448538878763, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hunter Armstrong and Caleb Dressel then finished strong as Team USA finished in first place with a time of 3:09.28, more than a second ahead of Australia.\", \"from\": 2638, \"to\": 2792, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2638, \"end\": 2654, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Armstrong\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hunter Armstrong\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Armstrong\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hunter_Armstrong\"}, {\"begin\": 2659, \"end\": 2664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kings_of_Leon\", \"score\": 0.9999999854717317, \"rank\": 1.4525232711762683e-08, \"text\": \"Caleb\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kings_of_Leon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kings_of_Leon\"}, {\"begin\": 2697, \"end\": 2705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9976628301718733, \"rank\": 0.0023426448538878763, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2782, \"end\": 2791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.999999962856237, \"rank\": 2.7295131491148477e-08, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was Alexy's first gold medal.\", \"from\": 2794, \"to\": 2826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Dressel now has eight golds, five of them in relay events.\", \"from\": 2827, \"to\": 2885, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Truly honored to be part of this relay and watching Caeleb finish that off for us and making Team USA proud,\\\"Alexy told the Associated Press.\", \"from\": 2887, \"to\": 3029, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2981, \"end\": 2989, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9976628301718733, \"rank\": 0.0023426448538878763, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3012, \"end\": 3028, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 0.9998480742441994, \"rank\": 0.0001441550434300463, \"text\": \"Associated Press\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"And starting off night one with a gold.\\\"\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3071, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States men's gymnastics team got off to a great start at the Paris Olympics early Saturday morning, but they did it despite a disappointing performance from one of their best competitors.\", \"from\": 3073, \"to\": 3271, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3077, \"end\": 3090, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999994833666703, \"rank\": 4.172411548901919e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Brody Malone, a multi-time national champion at Stanford before he graduated last year, had an uncharacteristically poor showing as he began his competition with a fall in the pommel horse, then ended it with a slip in his floor exercise.\", \"from\": 3273, \"to\": 3511, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3273, \"end\": 3278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\", \"score\": 0.9985576561163341, \"rank\": 0.0010239489708710324, \"text\": \"Brody\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nicholas_Brody\"}, {\"begin\": 3279, \"end\": 3285, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Malone\", \"score\": 0.7419949733291786, \"rank\": 0.34638336854412227, \"text\": \"Malone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Malone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Malone\"}, {\"begin\": 3321, \"end\": 3329, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1939028373032165e-25, \"text\": \"Stanford\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stanford_Cardinal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only returning member of the men's team that represented Team USA in Tokyo, Malone finished third among five U.S. athletes on the day, eliminating him from contention in all individual events.\", \"from\": 3513, \"to\": 3709, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3574, \"end\": 3582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9976628301718733, \"rank\": 0.0023426448538878763, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3586, \"end\": 3591, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.416665505438882e-14, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 3593, \"end\": 3599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Malone\", \"score\": 0.7419949733291786, \"rank\": 0.34638336854412227, \"text\": \"Malone\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Malone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mark_Malone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Malone had been coming off knee surgery that kept him out for much of the 2023 season, but he returned to Olympic trials in June and had a commanding performance, earning him a qualification for Paris.\", \"from\": 3711, \"to\": 3912, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3906, \"end\": 3911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.212082646559151e-13, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.or